com.whirvis.jraknet.peer

Interface RakNetPeerMessenger

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RakNetClient, RakNetClientPeer, RakNetPeer, RakNetServerPeer

    public interface RakNetPeerMessenger
    Represents an object that has the ability to send messages to a RakNetPeer.

    The reason these methods are not simply found within the original RakNetPeer class is to allow the interface to be implemented by the RakNetClient. This way, users are able to simply call the sendMessage(Reliability, Packet) method from the client without needing to get the actual RakNetServerPeer object first. Of course, calling from the client is just a shorthand and would be the exact same thing as grabbing the peer manually and then sending it a message.

    Since:
    JRakNet v2.11.0
    Author:
    Trent "Whirvis" Summerlin

        Sends a message to the peer.
        Parameters:
        reliability - the reliability of the packet.
        channel - the channel to send the packet on.
        packet - the packet to send.
        Returns:
        the generated encapsulated packet. This is normally not important, however it can be used for packet acknowledged and not acknowledged events if the reliability is of the WITH_ACK_RECEIPT type.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the reliability or packet are null.
